  "texts": [
    "An example of rubric verification data is shown in Figure 3.",
    "After SFT, we conduct a second RL stage on a broader set of rubric verifier prompts to improve our rubric verifier's generalization.",
    "During rollout, the verifier checks each criterion separately with a justification for the judgment (i.e., chain-of-thought reasoning) and obtains the binary judgment, and compares this judgment with the human expert's binary label -YES for this criteria check passed or NO if otherwise.",
    "The reward is calculated based on how closely the verifier's judgment matches the expert's judgment, measured as the ratio of agreement between the two.",
    "Note that this is an RLVR problem as the verifier outputs are binary signals, which we can easily match with the golden labels."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}